00:54:32.950 --> 00:54:35.430
rejected, and
basically was saying

00:54:35.430 --> 00:54:38.070
that she had been tricked.

00:54:38.070 --> 00:54:40.240
So my question,
coming full circle,

00:54:40.240 --> 00:54:44.940
is as you said,
passing is a privilege,

00:54:44.940 --> 00:54:47.110
and being attractive and
beautiful is a privilege.

00:54:47.110 --> 00:54:50.320
And having a voice for
that is a privilege.

00:54:50.320 --> 00:54:54.050
For the people who don't have
that privilege, who don't pass

00:54:54.050 --> 00:55:00.440
or who face lots of hardships
in their lives, how can we,

00:55:00.440 --> 00:55:03.040
or how-- this is kind of an
impossible question, maybe,

00:55:03.040 --> 00:55:06.770
but how can they
advocate for themselves

00:55:06.770 --> 00:55:08.010
without that privilege?

00:55:08.010 --> 00:55:12.190
Or how can we shape
a society that you

00:55:12.190 --> 00:55:17.290
can have more of a frame
for less privileged people.

00:55:17.290 --> 00:55:20.550
Let's say people who don't
pass, to have their own voice

00:55:20.550 --> 00:55:23.140
and not just look to
people who are passing.

00:55:26.020 --> 00:55:29.410
-I think that's an incredibly
convoluted question.

00:55:29.410 --> 00:55:31.720
It's layered in so many ways.

00:55:31.720 --> 00:55:34.530
Just in the framing
of it is problematic.

00:55:34.530 --> 00:55:37.220
What it broadcasts to
this entire room, I think,

00:55:37.220 --> 00:55:39.790
is problematic, too.

00:55:39.790 --> 00:55:41.580
It's difficult for
me to then break

00:55:41.580 --> 00:55:44.300
all of the layers of that down.

00:55:44.300 --> 00:55:50.540
But I think that all women and
girls, not just transwomen,

00:55:50.540 --> 00:55:53.440
are faced with impossible
images in media.

00:55:53.440 --> 00:55:59.000
So let's not just say transwomen
are grappling with that.

00:55:59.000 --> 00:56:02.590
Who are harming themselves
because of what the media has

00:56:02.590 --> 00:56:04.750
created as the image.

00:56:04.750 --> 00:56:07.740
So transwomen are
not only grappling

00:56:07.740 --> 00:56:11.060
with the idea of wanting
to-- some transwomen,

00:56:11.060 --> 00:56:13.570
we also have to be clear,
because not all transwomen's

00:56:13.570 --> 00:56:15.480
goal is to pass.

00:56:15.480 --> 00:56:18.850
I think that we are cognizant
that the system privileges

00:56:18.850 --> 00:56:21.460
folks that do pass and blend in.

00:56:21.460 --> 00:56:24.860
But I don't think that's
a goal for all transwomen.

00:56:24.860 --> 00:56:32.129
I feel incredibly, deeply sad
that this woman felt that way,

00:56:32.129 --> 00:56:33.170
and that was her journey.

00:56:33.170 --> 00:56:34.169
But that is her journey.

00:56:34.169 --> 00:56:37.350
I don't quite know it.

00:56:37.350 --> 00:56:42.180
In terms of folk in media and
what the media representation

00:56:42.180 --> 00:56:45.390
is, I think it's deeply flawed.

00:56:45.390 --> 00:56:48.810
I don't believe, again, that
all transwomen who are in media

00:56:48.810 --> 00:56:50.030
pass.

00:56:50.030 --> 00:56:52.160
I think a lot of them
would say that they don't.

00:56:52.160 --> 00:56:56.010
I do believe that a lot to
do subscribe and are allowed

00:56:56.010 --> 00:56:59.470
into the room, because there's
a certain layer of what I would

00:56:59.470 --> 00:57:03.570
say is acceptable femininity.

00:57:03.570 --> 00:57:06.130
A femininity that
is often celebrated.

00:57:06.130 --> 00:57:07.570
You can think about size.

00:57:07.570 --> 00:57:13.210
You can think about the ways in
which grooming is a part of it.

00:57:13.210 --> 00:57:16.320
Now do I believe that these
women are doing this in order

00:57:16.320 --> 00:57:17.770
to cater to?

00:57:17.770 --> 00:57:20.609
That I don't believe
that is a part of that.

00:57:20.609 --> 00:57:22.650
I believe that they are
showing up as themselves,

00:57:22.650 --> 00:57:24.340
and they are groomed in
the way that they believe

00:57:24.340 --> 00:57:25.965
that they want to
present to the world,

00:57:25.965 --> 00:57:28.010
and that is then
privileged and allowed in.

00:57:31.740 --> 00:57:41.630
But in terms of how do
we create a world-- how

00:57:41.630 --> 00:57:44.480
do we create a world, where--
right now what we're grappling

00:57:44.480 --> 00:57:47.520
with in the movement, I
think, is daily access issues

00:57:47.520 --> 00:57:48.020
for folk.

00:57:50.830 --> 00:57:52.600
How are you resourced?

00:57:52.600 --> 00:57:58.150
And one of the great ironies to
me is that transwomen of color

00:57:58.150 --> 00:58:02.610
specifically embody many
different identities,

00:58:02.610 --> 00:58:04.360
but rarely does all
those identities

00:58:04.360 --> 00:58:06.580
and those communities
show up for them.

00:58:06.580 --> 00:58:09.950
So we have feminist movements
that are dealing with gender.

00:58:09.950 --> 00:58:14.180
We have LGBT movements which
are supposed to be tasked

00:58:14.180 --> 00:58:16.090
with dealing with trans issues.

00:58:16.090 --> 00:58:18.220
And we have racial justice
movements, oftentimes

00:58:18.220 --> 00:58:20.130
that are not centered
around bodies that

00:58:20.130 --> 00:58:23.610
are not cisgender black males.

00:58:23.610 --> 00:58:26.444
And so there's no
coalition work in between,

00:58:26.444 --> 00:58:27.860
because everyone
says, well that's

00:58:27.860 --> 00:58:31.210
LGBT work that's supposed to
do with these trans people.

00:58:31.210 --> 00:58:32.970
But in with the LGBT
stuff, oftentimes

00:58:32.970 --> 00:58:35.890
the dominant narrative is
white, gay cisgender men.

00:58:35.890 --> 00:58:40.370
So that's the great
tragedy, I believe,

00:58:40.370 --> 00:58:42.110
in the existence for
transwomen of color.

00:58:42.110 --> 00:58:46.780
And I think at this
particular woman,

00:58:46.780 --> 00:58:50.640
based on what the
soundbites I just heard,

00:58:50.640 --> 00:58:52.780
was dealing with a lot of
trauma every single day,

00:58:52.780 --> 00:58:55.620
daily access trauma to
even leave their home.

00:58:55.620 --> 00:58:58.180
And so I think people
don't even understand

00:58:58.180 --> 00:59:03.150
what it takes for
people who are grappling

00:59:03.150 --> 00:59:06.190
with living their truth
to just leave their home,

00:59:06.190 --> 00:59:07.270
if they have a home.

00:59:11.640 --> 00:59:15.024
And so, all of that stuff Yeah.

00:59:15.024 --> 00:59:15.524
-Thank you.

00:59:18.450 --> 00:59:19.890
-Hello, my name is Beckett.

